%h2 How to find your local Dojo?
If you are interested in finding your local Dojo so you can start learning code or to mentor then <a href='http://zen.coderdojo.com/' target='_blank'>visit here</a> and enter your address. No Dojo in your area? Why not start one!

%h2 How to start a Dojo?
A CoderDojo Champion is a volunteer organiser who takes charge of setting up, running and maintaining a Dojo and following the CoderDojo ethos to facilitate young people to learn computer programming. 

There are five key steps to getting a Dojo up and running 
%ol 
  %li Become a CoderDojo Champion
  %li Gather your Team - Recruit a few technical/non technical volunteers
  %li Set a Date to Aim For 
  %li Find a Venue - schools, offices, libraries all make great Dojos
  %li Promote your Dojo - to friends, schools, social media 

